stories.text:
The state of streaming today is bad because you have to pay so many different services. If Netflix could have somehow prevented competition would we be better off? The consumer could pay only one sub and watch everything there.

Do you think in some cases a monopoly is justifiable and even good for society?
stories.title: Ask HN: Would we be better off if Netflix maintained a monopoly?
